solutionCode.javascript:
    ```javascript
function numberOfColoredCells(n) {
    return n * n + (n - 1) * (n - 1);
}
```

    For each minute, the boundary of colored cells expands outward in a square pattern. To get the total number of colored cells, we consider two squares - the inner square formed by the cells that were colored at minute n-1, and the outer square formed by the cells that were colored at minute n. 

The inner square has dimensions (n-1)x(n-1), while the outer square has dimensions nxn. The number of colored cells is the sum of the areas of these two squares.

We compute this as `n * n + (n - 1) * (n - 1)`.

